	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">Interesting thread indeed. But before you all go nuts on the above mentioned issue, I'd like to quote what is probably the most intelligent comment on that thread:<br />
<br />
<table border="0" align="center" width="90%" cellpadding="3" cellspacing="1"><tr><td><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#FFFFFF"><b>quote:</b></font></td></tr><tr><td style="BORDER: #000000 1px solid; FONT-SIZE: 11px; COLOR: #FFFFFF; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana,Arial; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #4D4D73;">I can't believe that there is this much concern over the EQ economy. I actually took economics, and my instructor called this phenomenon the "Peter Pan Principle" and it is real.<br />
<br />
If you think its true, it becomes true. <br />
<br />
For example:<br />
<br />
If the real world thinks that there is inflation, then every goes out and buys stuff now, before prices go up, thereby creating a demand which in turn raises prices.<br />
<br />
The same works with deflation, where people will stop buying to wait for the prices to go down, thereby creating a deflationary trend.<br />
<br />
Sure there are exploits that people take advantage of, as soon as SOE hears about it, they fix it. Its a constant battle, but this battle has been around for years. This is not a new problem that just happened in the last month. There is no need to panic. We will all be fine.<br />
<br />
This original post is kind of like the local news when they do a breaking story that there is a new computer virus out there. That used to create panic, but the fact is that there are maybe millions of viruses out there. The anti-virus companies make a new update or MS does an emergency, patch and all is well.<br />
<br />
Its panic letters by an admitted plat seller that makes the prices go up. Now many people have read this thread and are going to get that CoF for 70k before the price goes up. Nformnu did a good job of creating more business for himself, too bad he didn't raise his prices sooner, he could have made 8 million plat instead of the measly 4 million. Gratz.<br />
<br />
Most of you believe him, but if you would for a second stop the panic, and not rush out and buy the high end items you think are going to go up in value, the prices will stabilize.<br />
<br />
We can all create the inflation and blame it on Ebay or Duping, terms that have been around for years, or just play the game, enjoy it and not panic over a situation that has existed for years. Back a few years ago, there was a hack in which you could create any item you wanted. Somehow we all lived through that one.</td></tr></table></font></p>
	
	<p></p>
	<p></p>
	</td></tr></table>
	<!-- Main Post Body -->
	</td>
</tr>
