	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">I agree with Gurm.  It could be just me, but I have a really hard time believing this.  To me it sounds like the emails that go around talking about terrorists buying courier uniforms, and people being drugged and having a kidney harvested.  It speaks to our fears without offering any proof, and relies on panic to motivate us to make bad decisions.<br />
<br />
There's enough truth in it to make the reader stop and give it serious consideration.  Yes, buying characters and platinum is 'bad' in most people mind (it is in mine, this is supposed to just be a game, not an olympic event where you have to win).  But that's pretty much all conventional wisdom.<br />
<br />
I have a good friend in the game that does tradeskills.  He made armor for me, and told me recently about a problem where a merchant in Thurgadin had something needed for blacksmithing that he was giving away after a patch.  Sony stopped it within one day.  It's clear to me that they still are concerned about the ecomony.  People that sell plat, aren't concerned about you or me.  They are concerned about their own profits.<br />
<br />
The poster says that the duplication process has gone unchecked for 2 months.  If he knows this, and is genuinely concerned, why not post the process publically.  That would force sony to act by bringing the servers down and fixing the issue <b>today</b>.  Oh, but wait!  That might stop him from being able to duplicate platinum to continue running his business.<br />
<br />
It's good to be concerned about your community.  It's not good to let some anonymous poster spread rumor and unsubstantiated statements to generate panic.<br />
<br />
<br />
Ysgarlad<br />
Level 41 cleric<br />
Keeper of "Innoruuk's Big Book of Hate"</font></p>
	
