	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">another thing I thought of while reading this thread was what I do when I hit the bazaar with loot that neither of my 2 alts or I can use...I check what someone else has the items listed for and undersell them by a little to make quick plat.<br />
<br />
sounds ok right?...well a few things to think about:<br />
<br />
1)I have walked in and not found an item so i look at it's stats and price it at what I think it is worth and/or do a PC (some people have no clue and just want to join the conversation so they give a made up value)<br />
<br />
2)some of the values I have gotten off other vendors and price checks have been astronomically high i.e. I look at a spell and say "well i guess it is more rare than i thought" and place said high price on it which then leads to the next few people that come in and look at my price go "man I didn't know we could get that much for this PoS" then they place said high price on the item/spell (I bought fortitude for 1.5k before i noticed it was a 2x downgrade to the current buff i have<img src="images/smilies/crying.gif" border="0" alt="Crying">  ) ***side note you can no longer group with a lowbie and give them heroic bond or other HP/AC buff---just noticed today***<br />
<br />
OK getting tired here...<br />
<br />
3)player run casinos have helped hinder the economy (newbies that /q when they lose a big bet)<br />
<br />
4)if SOE makes all spells below 60 vendor buyable, Skyfire will be useless except for the shards that we clerics need for our epics...try getting a pick-up group to help you in SF when all spells that drop are vendor buyable...this will also kill the bazaar prices for any dropped spell<br />
<br />
5)It is a game...and just a game...the economy will sway differently on each server the economy will sway in real life...it happens.  Supply and demand will effect prices differently on each server.  If you get an item you don't know what does put a price on it based on how hard it was to get or how useful it sounds...this way more people can afford a fungi tunic, and more people will be able to buy spells in the bazaar and not have to camp 3 weeks for a spell they may never use, and I can't complain enough about how it sucked to be KS'd 4 times when lvl 29 camping Hadden with a friend.<br />
<br />
6)just have fun---after all it is just a game<br />
<br />
<br />
sorry for the rant it is 4:52 in the morning here and I have tried to catch all of my ranting typos...I will probably come back and read this later and say WTF was I thinking hitting submit reply...but such is life<br />
<br />
<br />
btw h8t cheaters =P<br />
